    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it feels like you're saying the border security argument is basically just an excuse for exclusion. if we admit that human rights are the \"higher\" standard, doesn't that mean any policy that prioritizes a border over a person's safety is inherently immoral? like, is there actually any legitimate moral value left in the sovereignty argument once you've said human rights are superior?",
