      "content": "The sovereignty argument is not inherently immoral, but it becomes morally compromised when it is used as an absolute shield against basic human decency. A legitimate moral value in sovereignty is the right of a nation to self-govern and maintain domestic order, which is a necessary prerequisite for any stable society. However, this right is not absolute and must yield when it directly conflicts with the fundamental, non-negotiable right to life and safety.",
